<h1>Disputed sightings</h1>
<p class="subhead">Law IX.</p>

<blockquote class="survey-note">
  Unverified. The Survey does not endorse.
</blockquote>

<p>
  This guide depicts everything, so the unreliable thing here is not the
  image but the claim. When a naturalist reports an organism the established
  ecology cannot yet account for — something seen at the edge of a vent's
  light that eats nothing on the record, or fits no mapped biome — it is
  filed here: drawn, but unverified, until a successor either validates it
  into the ecology or dissents it into oblivion.
</p>

<p>
  <em>No disputed sightings have been filed yet.</em>
</p>
